                            <comment id="14454619" author="drothmaler" created="Tue, 10 Aug 2010 04:07:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems that &quot;java.library.path&quot; can&apos;t be changed, using the System.setProperty method (see: &lt;a href=&quot;http://bugs.sun.com/bugdatabase/view_bug.do?bug_id=4280189&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://bugs.sun.com/bugdatabase/view_bug.do?bug_id=4280189&lt;/a&gt;), as it is done by the SurefireBooter. So there should be a special handling for such read-only properties (conversion to &quot;-D&quot; commandline arguments) or at least it would be nice, if the &quot;systemPropertyVariables&quot; documentation would contain an hint, that they are configured using &quot;System.setProperty&quot; and that this may not work for some properties like &quot;java.library.path&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14454928" author="krosenvold" created="Fri, 4 Mar 2011 12:42:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Surefire now emits a warning log message upon attempting to set this property. Fixed in r1078097&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17994034" author="olamy" created="Fri, 4 Jul 2025 07:14:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-surefire/issues/1947&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven-surefire#1947&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
